• Editor's note: This article is updated each time new information becomes available. JOHANNESBURG - Ace Magashule remains ANC Secretary General by nine votes. Senzo Mchunu has been allocated another 15 votes. Currently, the ANC's steering committee is in a meeting with Elexion officials. This follows an issue surrounding the missing ballot papers for the secretary general position. Meanwhile, lawyers for the ANC in KwaZulu-Natal and Limpopo are awaiting instructions to go to court to challenge the missing papers. READ: 'Missing' votes will be sorted out: ANC provincial chairman Advocate Dali Mpofu is leading the legal team. They plan to challenge issues around missing ballot papers for the ANC Secretary General position. eNCA